com.pump.data

Class Key<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.data.Key<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object this Key relates to.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.CharSequence

    public class Key<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.CharSequence, java.io.Serializable
    This describes a key/attribute and its associated generic type.

    This also includes optional BoundsCheckers which are triggered in the validate(Object) method.

    Each Key is also capable of serializing/deserializing an object as a String. The Key class itself is abstract, and each subclass knows how to read/write data itself.
